mp one dependency to a new version. Write the modified manifest to disk. Read it back and verify: (1) only the target dependency version changed, (2) all other entries are identical, (3) formatting, comments, and key order are preserved.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The auto-generated pull request is created on the real repository with the correct single-dependency diff.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"A Unit test with mocked GitHub API and Git diff could miss real failures: Git diff generation depends on current repository state (what's already committed), and actual PR creation on GitHub may fail for reasons the mock doesn't catch. The behavior explicitly requires testing 'on the real repository', implying real Git subprocess calls and real GitHub API. System-level testing is necessary to catch both diff-generation errors and GitHub API failures.","test_description":"Create a test Git repository with a manifest containing a vulnerable dependency. Run the scanner's PR-creation logic. Verify a PR is created with a diff that changes only the vulnerable dependency's version (single-line or minimal change). Verify the PR branch is clean, commit message is correct, and diff matches the intended change. Test with real GitHub API call or test GitHub instance.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A major version bump is correctly identified as a breaking change based on semver comparison.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is pure semver comparison logic with no I/O, external dependencies, or LLM involvement. A Unit test with version string pairs is sufficient to catch comparison errors (off-by-one in parsing, wrong operators, mishandled pre-releases).","test_description":"Test the semver-comparison function w